cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on improving the accuracy of convolutional neural networks on image classification tasks. It also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a method for automatic architecture search. Additionally, it may fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves developing algorithms for improving the performance of neural networks. Neural networks (cs.NE) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with designing the architecture of convolutional neural networks. Finally, data structures (cs.DS) may also be relevant as the paper proposes a method for efficiently exploring the number of channels in a neural network while controlling the number of parameters.
